<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-09-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-09-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="833" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d833">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Léger</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Haiti</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-09-15"><hi rend="italic">September 15,
                                    1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary of State</hi>: I hasten to inform you
                            that I have returned to Washington. I was sorry to hear, on my landing
                            at New York, the sorrowful news of the Galveston disaster. Permit me to
                            join in the mourning of so many distressed families and to lament with
                            you the losses that the country has just sustained.</p>
                        <p>Be pleased to accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">J. N. Léger.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>